cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on social recommendation over online communities. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper proposes a new probabilistic entity matching scheme for identifying the relevance score of a streaming item to a user. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel Bi-Layer Hidden Markov Model for capturing user behaviors and interactions. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is possible as the paper proposes a new indexing scheme called {\Tree} for improving the efficiency of the solution. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also possible as the paper deals with handling a huge number of users over high speed streams, which requires efficient data management techniques.
